reviewText:
Sadly I can't recommend this Anniversary version.

TL;DR - Get the original Fable: The Lost Chapters for 1/4th of the price of this Anniversary version.
---------

Fable still a very good game, specially considering when it was made (10 years ago, already?). However:

1 - While it was great for its time, the game didn't age so well. Mostly because other games took this formula and improved it (which was a natural thing to happen);
2 - This remake still has A LOT of bugs, glitches and things like that. While the textures are good, the models still the same as 10 years ago, with lots of clipping and ugly things;
3 - And not ALL the game has been remade for nicer looking graphics. There's still some Low-Rez bits, like the cut-scenes. Shame, really;
4 - You simply can't pay 4x the price of the current Fable: The Lost Chapters for having some new HD textures.

Fable Anniversary has been a MAJOR disappointment to me. For the price I was expecting a hell lot more than just new HD textures.

